Subclasses of XUIComponentBase in netgest.bo.xwc.framework.components
 class XUICommand
          XUICommand is a UIComponent that represents a user interface component which, when activated by the user, triggers an application specific "command" or "action".
 class XUIForm
          XUIForm is a UIComponent that represents an input form to be presented to the user, and whose child components represent (among other things) the input fields to be included when the form is submitted.
 class XUIInput
          XUIInput is a XUIComponentBase that represents a component that both displays output to the user (like UIOutput components do) and processes request parameters on the subsequent request that need to be decoded.
 class XUIOption
           
 class XUIOutput
          XUIOutput is a UIComponent that has a value, optionally retrieved from a model tier bean via a value expression, that is displayed to the user.
